00:12:33.24 --> 00:12:35.10
is also on hold for now.

00:12:35.10 --> 00:12:36.81
You play with fire, you get burned.

00:12:36.81 --> 00:12:38.58
And here, Russia strikes again.

00:12:38.58 --> 00:12:42.72
Travis Tygart is CEO of the US Anti-Doping Agency.

00:12:42.72 --> 00:12:45.21
She's going to be skating with a dark cloud hanging

00:12:45.21 --> 00:12:45.96
over her head.

00:12:45.96 --> 00:12:47.67
But at the end of the day, other athletes

00:12:47.67 --> 00:12:49.62
are there who want the results to be

00:12:49.62 --> 00:12:51.15
final at the end of the competition

00:12:51.15 --> 00:12:54.90
and have their national anthem played.

00:12:54.90 --> 00:12:57.21
We spoke with US figure skater Nathan Chen

00:12:57.21 --> 00:13:00.35
last week about potentially losing out on a ceremony.

00:13:00.35 --> 00:13:01.89
Regardless of the color of the medal,

00:13:01.89 --> 00:13:04.50
I think just knowing, one, that US has a medal, and two,

00:13:04.50 --> 00:13:06.75
to be able to share that moment and step on the podium

00:13:06.75 --> 00:13:08.43
and go through the whole ceremony together,

00:13:08.43 --> 00:13:09.27
it's really special.

00:13:09.27 --> 00:13:10.20
Erin Jackson--

00:13:10.20 --> 00:13:13.14
Team USA continues to add to its medal count.

00:13:13.14 --> 00:13:14.43
Here she comes--

00:13:14.43 --> 00:13:17.82
Speed skater Erin Jackson whose friend Brittany Bowe gave up

00:13:17.82 --> 00:13:20.07
her own spot so Jackson could compete,

00:13:20.07 --> 00:13:24.12
race to gold in the 500 meters, becoming the first Black woman

00:13:24.12 --> 00:13:25.95
to win a medal in her sport.

00:13:25.95 --> 00:13:31.13
Erin Jackson's meteoric rise to the top.

00:13:31.13 --> 00:13:33.95
In another win for Team USA, women's hockey

00:13:33.95 --> 00:13:35.87
beat Finland to head to the finals.

00:13:35.87 --> 00:13:39.71
It is the sixth time US and its archrival Canada

00:13:39.71 --> 00:13:41.36
will battle for the gold.

00:13:41.36 --> 00:13:42.29
Norah.

00:13:42.29 --> 00:13:44.78
Oh yeah, I'm rooting for the US Women's Hockey Team.

00:13:44.78 --> 00:13:46.58
Jamie, thank you.

00:13:46.58 --> 00:13:48.50
All right, we go now from the capital of China

00:13:48.50 --> 00:13:51.54
to the new capital of the football world, Los Angeles.

00:13:51.54 --> 00:13:54.11
The City of Angels is now the City of Champions

00:13:54.11 --> 00:13:57.29
after their Los Angeles Rams beat the Cincinnati Bengals

00:13:57.29 --> 00:14:00.18
23-20 in Super Bowl LVI.

00:14:00.18 --> 00:14:02.21
CBS's Carter Evans has the highlights

00:14:02.21 --> 00:14:04.91
of the big game and that historic halftime show.

00:14:04.91 --> 00:14:08.65


00:14:08.65 --> 00:14:11.13
Pass.

00:14:11.13 --> 00:14:12.78
Got it, touchdown.

00:14:12.78 --> 00:14:15.27
That's Super Bowl MVP Cooper Kupp

00:14:15.27 --> 00:14:18.60
with the game winning touchdown at a showdown straight out

00:14:18.60 --> 00:14:19.47
of Hollywood.

00:14:19.47 --> 00:14:26.76
Finally, it is time for the Super Bowl.

00:14:26.76 --> 00:14:29.67
Los Angeles delivered a star-studded Super Bowl.

00:14:29.67 --> 00:14:33.42
Jay Z, Matt Damon, J.Lo, and Ben Affleck in the stands.

00:14:33.42 --> 00:14:35.09
West Coast make some noise.

00:14:35.09 --> 00:14:37.78


00:14:37.78 --> 00:14:39.97
LeBron James was loving every minute

00:14:39.97 --> 00:14:42.13
of the ground breaking hip-hop halftime show led

00:14:42.13 --> 00:14:45.46
by Dr. Dre and Snoop Dogg.

00:14:45.46 --> 00:14:47.77
It's the one and only D-R-E.

00:14:47.77 --> 00:14:49.63
Dr. Dre--

00:14:49.63 --> 00:14:53.66
In the final minute, the game was sealed by Aaron Donald.

00:14:53.66 --> 00:14:55.28
I am so happy.

00:14:55.28 --> 00:14:56.32
I wanted this so bad.

00:14:56.32 --> 00:14:58.51
I dreamed this, man.

00:14:58.51 --> 00:15:01.44
I dreamed this, and it's like-- it's surreal.

00:15:01.44 --> 00:15:02.49
Look at this--

00:15:02.49 --> 00:15:06.75
An emotional victory for so many players and 36-year-old Sean

00:15:06.75 --> 00:15:11.97
McVay, now the youngest coach ever to win a Super Bowl.

00:15:11.97 --> 00:15:14.52
In addition to the Super Bowl ring, Rams' safety,

00:15:14.52 --> 00:15:16.68
Taylor Rapp had an engagement ring

00:15:16.68 --> 00:15:18.27
for his longtime girlfriend.

00:15:18.27 --> 00:15:20.31
And wide receiver Van Jefferson's wife

00:15:20.31 --> 00:15:22.23
went into labor during the game.

00:15:22.23 --> 00:15:25.62
By the end of the night, he was holding his newborn son.

00:15:25.62 --> 00:15:28.53
Rams' quarterback Matthew Stafford capped off the win

00:15:28.53 --> 00:15:31.29
with his girls in a shower of confetti,

00:15:31.29 --> 00:15:33.36
a perfect ending for the first Super Bowl

00:15:33.36 --> 00:15:34.98
at the Rams' new stadium.

00:15:34.98 --> 00:15:36.01
Let's do it again.

00:15:36.01 --> 00:15:39.05
Let's do it again next year.

00:15:39.05 --> 00:15:42.56
And the city of LA is so proud of this Super Bowl win

00:15:42.56 --> 00:15:44.45
that they're actually changing the Hollywood

00:15:44.45 --> 00:15:46.70
sign to read Rams' House.

00:15:46.70 --> 00:15:49.04
They're also planning a victory parade

00:15:49.04 --> 00:15:51.23
to honor the team on Wednesday.

00:15:51.23 --> 00:15:52.01
Norah.

00:15:52.01 --> 00:15:54.20
I can see the construction already underway.

00:15:54.20 --> 00:15:55.41
Carter Evans, thanks.

00:15:55.41 --> 00:15:56.87
All right, still ahead on tonight's

00:15:56.87 --> 00:15:59.63
CBS Evening News, how a flight attendant saved the day

00:15:59.63 --> 00:16:02.66
with a coffee pot after an unruly passenger tried

00:16:02.66 --> 00:16:04.40
to storm the cockpit.

00:16:04.40 --> 00:16:07.37
Freedom after 44 years behind the bars for a crime

00:16:07.37 --> 00:16:09.30
he says he did not commit.

00:16:09.30 --> 00:16:10.76
And we remember.

00:16:10.76 --> 00:16:13.55
Ivan Reitman the director of Ghostbusters and so many

00:16:13.55 --> 00:16:14.90
other classic comedies.

00:16:14.90 --> 00:16:21.30


00:16:21.30 --> 00:16:23.76
Passengers aboard a flight from LA to DC on Sunday

00:16:23.76 --> 00:16:26.58
feared for their lives when an unruly passenger

00:16:26.58 --> 00:16:28.23
tried to storm the cockpit.

00:16:28.23 --> 00:16:30.99
Well, a quick-thinking American Airlines flight attendant

00:16:30.99 --> 00:16:34.49
grabbed a coffee pot and yet bashed the man in the head.

00:16:34.49 --> 00:16:36.45
A crowd of people held him down until the plane

00:16:36.45 --> 00:16:40.15
made an emergency landing in Kansas City.

00:16:40.15 --> 00:16:41.32
All right, breaking tonight.

00:16:41.32 --> 00:16:44.04
A man who has proclaimed his innocence for 44 years

00:16:44.04 --> 00:16:45.54
is celebrating his freedom.

00:16:45.54 --> 00:16:48.57
A Louisiana judge ruled today that Vincent Simmons did not

00:16:48.57 --> 00:16:52.05
get a fair trial when he was convicted in 1977

00:16:52.05 --> 00:16:53.97
of attempted aggravated rape.

00:16:53.97 --> 00:16:56.31
The judge gave Simmons what he'd long

00:16:56.31 --> 00:16:57.76
been asking for-- a new trial.

00:16:57.76 --> 00:17:00.33
But the district attorney said he won't retry Simmons,

00:17:00.33 --> 00:17:03.51
so Simmons went free.

00:17:03.51 --> 00:17:05.01
All right, tributes continue to pour

00:17:05.01 --> 00:17:06.57
in tonight for producer and director

00:17:06.57 --> 00:17:09.27
Ivan Reitman who died unexpectedly on Sunday.

00:17:09.27 --> 00:17:12.21
Reitman's numerous credits include the classic comedies

00:17:12.21 --> 00:17:15.72
Ghostbusters, Animal House, Kindergarten Cop,

00:17:15.72 --> 00:17:17.49
and Space Jam.

00:17:17.49 --> 00:17:19.83
Reitman's movie-making son, Jason,

00:17:19.83 --> 00:17:22.47
says his dad came from a family of survivors

00:17:22.47 --> 00:17:25.56
and he turned his legacy into laughter.

00:17:25.56 --> 00:17:28.71
Ivan Reitman was 75 years old.

00:17:28.71 --> 00:17:31.86
And coming up-- how a New Jersey mom solved a problem

00:17:31.86 --> 00:17:37.59
in the cookie industry and built an empire while she was at it.

00:17:37.59 --> 00:17:40.81
If you can't watch the CBS Evening News, you can listen.

00:17:40.81 --> 00:17:42.97
Subscribe wherever you get your podcasts.

00:17:42.97 --> 00:17:44.82
Sponsored by Principal Financial Group.

00:17:44.82 --> 00:17:49.97


00:17:49.97 --> 00:17:52.34
What better way to end this Valentine's Day

00:17:52.34 --> 00:17:54.29
than a sweet story about a mother's love

00:17:54.29 --> 00:17:56.28
for her child and cookies.

00:17:56.28 --> 00:17:59.99
Here's CBS's Elaine Quijano.

00:17:59.99 --> 00:18:03.14
Denise Woodard knows rejection in business.

00:18:03.14 --> 00:18:06.21
You were rejected by not one, not two,

00:18:06.21 --> 00:18:07.62
but how many investors?

00:18:07.62 --> 00:18:09.38
At least 86.

00:18:09.38 --> 00:18:10.61
86, that must have hurt.

00:18:10.61 --> 00:18:11.39
You know, it was.

00:18:11.39 --> 00:18:13.01
I took it pretty personal.

00:18:13.01 --> 00:18:15.53
But her mission was personal too.

00:18:15.53 --> 00:18:20.54
Years ago, her baby Vivian ate a snack and ended up in the ER.

00:18:20.54 --> 00:18:23.33
That's how we learned that she's actually allergic to corn.

00:18:23.33 --> 00:18:25.56
And what went through your mind at that point?

00:18:25.56 --> 00:18:28.28
I realized that life-threatening food allergies are just

00:18:28.28 --> 00:18:30.23
that they're life-threatening and that I

00:18:30.23 --> 00:18:32.48
needed to come up with a solution to make

00:18:32.48 --> 00:18:33.86
her life a little easier.

00:18:33.86 --> 00:18:34.75
Add the water.

00:18:34.75 --> 00:18:35.33
Yep.

00:18:35.33 --> 00:18:38.57
Vivian is one of an estimated 5.6 million children

00:18:38.57 --> 00:18:40.61
in the US with a food allergy.

00:18:40.61 --> 00:18:43.97
In 2016, Woodard launched Partake Foods,

00:18:43.97 --> 00:18:46.04
a line of allergy friendly cookies

00:18:46.04 --> 00:18:47.96
so kids wouldn't feel left out.

00:18:47.96 --> 00:18:50.90
But the company struggled until Woodard,

00:18:50.90 --> 00:18:53.18
the daughter of Black and Korean parents,

00:18:53.18 --> 00:18:56.18
connected with Black investors, including

00:18:56.18 --> 00:18:59.66
singer Rihanna and Jay Z's venture capital fund.

00:18:59.66 --> 00:19:03.89
Today, 8,000 retailers nationwide carry her products.

00:19:03.89 --> 00:19:06.38
What do you hope Vivian learns from watching you?

00:19:06.38 --> 00:19:08.36
The fact that she thinks that's normal

00:19:08.36 --> 00:19:10.97
and that it's OK and can be celebrated

00:19:10.97 --> 00:19:12.47
is what I hope for her.

00:19:12.47 --> 00:19:13.82
Too hot?

00:19:13.82 --> 00:19:16.58
Tackling challenges baked into the industry

00:19:16.58 --> 00:19:19.91
and finding new ingredients for success.

00:19:19.91 --> 00:19:24.17
Elaine Quijano, CBS News, New York.

00:19:24.17 --> 00:19:25.82
Love a mom-preneur.

00:19:25.82 --> 00:19:28.26
We'll be right back.

